title: Russia Penalizes Google For Retaining Banned Content: Reuters
text: Alphabet Inc's (NASDAQ: GOOG) (NASDAQ: GOOGL) Google paid Russia over 32 million roubles ($455,079) in fines for failing to delete content Moscow deems illegal, Reuters reports. Russia last week said it would seek to penalize Google a percentage of its annual Russian turnover later this month for regularly failing to delete banned content on its search engine and YouTube.
